<p>You don&rsquo;t need a gym to stay healthy.<br /> Start by walking short distances instead of driving. Use the stairs instead of the elevator whenever possible. At home, stretch or do bodyweight exercises such as squats, planks, and push-ups. Try to move your body at least 30 minutes every day. Even small movements during the day &mdash; like cleaning or gardening &mdash; can make a difference. The goal is to stay active in simple and enjoyable ways.</p>','The text encourages people to stay active through everyday actions, not just workouts.','Going to the gym is the only way to stay healthy and fit.','Doing household chores can count as physical activity.','The main idea is to exercise intensely for short periods only.','','TRUE,FALSE','1,2,1,2','0','4');
