<p>Here are five practical tips for healthy eating that can guide you toward making better food choices.&nbsp; The cornerstone of a healthy diet is consuming the right amount of calories based on your activity level, ensuring that the energy you take in matches the energy you expend. If you consume more energy than your body requires, the excess will be stored as fat, leading to weight gain. Conversely, if you consume too few calories, you will lose weight.</p>
